equires excellent drainage. Benefits from afternoon shade in summer. Gray-green foliage more drought-tolerant. Not ideal for prolonged humid periods.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, international suppliers"}, {"name": "''Sissinghurst''", "slug": "sissinghurst", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "England, named after Sissinghurst Castle Garden", "traits": "Dwarf variety 30cm tall, large bright green leaves, compact mounding habit", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Moderate, smaller plant = less total harvest but good leaf-to-flower ratio", "growing_notes": "Excellent for humid subtropical climates container growing and small gardens. Lower height reduces wind damage. Good for edging. Needs very good drainage. Bright foliage more susceptible to sunburn - provide afternoon shade.", "availability": "Beth Chatto Gardens (UK), specialty international suppliers"}, {"name": "Hyssopus officinalis f. albus (White Hyssop)", "slug": "hyssopus-officinalis-f-albus-white-hyssop", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "Natural form, Southern Europe, cultivated for centuries", "traits": "50-60cm tall, dark green leaves, slightly more upright than blue form", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Similar to standard blue variety, good leaf and flower production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "''Alba''", "slug": "alba", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "European white cultivar selection", "traits": "Compact 60cm, dark green foliage, bushy habit", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good, compact plants produce well", "growing_notes": "Selected for improved white flower form. Good for humid subtropical climates with proper care. Plant in raised beds with excellent drainage. Benefits from organic mulch to keep roots cool in summer heat. Prune hard in spring.", "availability": "North Car