lly distributed", "traits": "Creeping herb <30cm tall, spreading 90cm, succulent oblong leaves 4-6mm thick", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT FOR humid subtropical climates! Thrives in wetland areas, bog gardens, pond edges. Perfect for Humid subtropical wet conditions that challenge true hyssop. Grows in waterlogged soil or even submerged in shallow water. Can tolerate brackish conditions. Good ground cover for wet areas. Hardy Zones 8-11. Used in Ayurvedic medicine for cognitive enhancement.", "availability": "Native to Australia - available at aquatic plant nurseries, bog garden specialists"}, {"name": "Bacopa monnieri (Kerala Native Brahmi)", "slug": "bacopa-monnieri-kerala-native-brahmi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "Indigenous to India, including tropical monsoon climates - grows naturally in marshy areas throughout the region", "traits": "Creeping perennial herb, 15cm tall, succulent oblong leaves arranged oppositely, forms dense mat", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High - fast-growing, can be harvested continuously. Leaves are the medicinal part.", "growing_notes": "IDEAL FOR tropical monsoon climates! This is what should be grown instead of Hyssopus officinalis in tropical monsoon climates. Perfectly adapted to monsoon climate - actually requires constant moisture. Thrives in waterlogged soil. Can be grown in: (1) Bog gardens; (2) Pond edges; (3) Paddy field borders; (4) Water gardens; (5) Hydroponic systems; (6) Containers kept constantly wet. Traditional Ayurvedic herb for memory, cognitive function, anxiety relief. Extensively used in tropical monsoon climates traditional medicine.", "availability": "Widely available throughout tropical monsoon climates - local Ayurvedic plant nurseries, traditional medicine suppliers, agricultural centers, can be collected from wild populations (with permission)"}, {"name": "Kerala Local Ecotypes", "slug": "kerala-local